{{unreferenced|date=August 2012}} {{ Infobox V8 Supercar race report | flag = Tasmania | title = 2012 Falken Tasmania Challenge | round_no = 2 | season_no = 15 | year = 2012 | series = IVSC | track_map = Symmons Plains Raceway (Australia) track map.svg | date = 29 March–1 April | location = [[Launceston, Tasmania|Launceston]], [[Tasmania]] | circuit = Symmons Plains Raceway | weather = Fine | race1_laps = 59 | race1_dist = 140 | pole1 = [[Mark Winterbottom]] | pole1_team = [[Ford Performance Racing]] | pole1_time = 51.4020 | winner1 = [[Will Davison]] | winner1_team = [[Ford Performance Racing]] | winner1_time = 52:30.5485 | race2_laps = 84 | race2_dist = 200 | pole2 = [[Craig Lowndes]] | pole2_team = [[Triple Eight Race Engineering (Australia)|Triple Eight Race Engineering]] | pole2_time = 51.0408 | winner2 = [[Jamie Whincup]] | winner2_team = [[Triple Eight Race Engineering (Australia)|Triple Eight Race Engineering]] | winner2_time = 1:17:31.3871 }}
The '''2012 [[Falken Tasmania Challenge]]''' was a motor race for the Australian sedan-based [[V8 Supercars]]. It was the second event of the [[2012 International V8 Supercars Championship]]. It was held on the weekend of 30 March–1 April at the [[Symmons Plains Raceway]], near [[Launceston, Tasmania|Launceston]], [[Tasmania]].
Race 3 of the championship was won by Victorian Ford driver [[Will Davison]] from [[Ford Performance Racing]]. Race 4, held the following day was won by fellow Victorian, [[Jamie Whincup]] driving a Holden for [[Triple Eight Race Engineering (Australia)|Triple Eight Race Engineering]]. Davison's third place in race four made him the leading performer of the event.
