The '''Hero Asian Champions Trophy 2018''' was held at [[Muscat]], Oman between October 18–28, 2018. It was the fifth edition of the [[Asian Hockey Champions Trophy]], a [[field hockey]] tournament for the six best [[Asia|Asian]] national teams. This was announced by the [[Asian Hockey Federation]] (AHF) on 29 January 2018. The Oman Hockey Association hosted the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hero Asian Champions Trophy to be hosted by Oman Hockey Association |url=http://www.asiahockey.org/news/event-allocation-ceremony-hero-asian-champions-trophy-2018/|publisher=AHF|accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref>

The 5th edition of the biennial event took place at the [[Sultan Qaboos Sports Complex]] in [[Muscat]], Sultanate of Oman. The tournament featured host nation [[Oman men's national field hockey team|Oman]], [[Pakistan men's national field hockey team|Pakistan]], [[Malaysia men's national field hockey team|Malaysia]], [[India men's national field hockey team|India]], [[South Korea men's national field hockey team|South Korea]], and [[Japan men's national field hockey team|Japan]].

[[Hero MotoCorp]], a global partner of the International Hockey Federation (FIH) and a long-term associate of the Asian Hockey Federation (AHF), were the title sponsor of the tournament.

Pakistan and India were declared joint winners by virtue of forfeiture of the final due to persistent rain and Malaysia finished at the 3rd place after defeating Japan 3-2 in the penalty shootouts in the bronze medal match.<ref name="Final">{{cite web |title=Pakistan and India Are Declared Joint Champions in the 5th Edition of the Asian Champions Trophy |url=http://www.asiahockey.org/news/pakistan-and-india-are-declared-joint-champions-in-the-5th-edition-of-the-asian-champions-trophy/ |website=asiahockey.org |accessdate=29 October 2018 |date=28 October 2018}}</ref> Malaysia's [[Faizal Saari]] was the top scorer of the tournament with 8 Goals. India remained the only undefeated team in the tournament.

==Umpires==
A total of nine umpires were appointed by the [[International Hockey Federation|FIH]] and National Association to officiate the tournament.<ref>[https://tms.fih.ch/competitions/961#officials Officials]</ref>
