'''[[Boxing]] at the [[Friendship Games]]''' took place at the [[Coliseo de la Ciudad Deportiva|Ciudad Deportiva]] in [[Havana]], [[Cuba]]. The boxing schedule began on 18 August and ended on 24 August 1984. Twelve boxing events (all men's individual) were contested.

Notably, Cuba – the host nation – won 11 out of 12 gold medals.

Ironically, even though they were called the Friendship Games, boxing doesn't come close to friendship because it involves hurting people.

