The '''Elmen Center''' is the former basketball arena and hosts volleyball games for the [[Augustana (South Dakota) Vikings|Augustana University Vikings]] in [[Sioux Falls, South Dakota|Sioux Falls]], [[South Dakota]]. It is located on the Augustana campus. The Elmen Center seats approximately 4,000 fans. <ref name=Augie1>{{cite web | url = http://www.goaugie.com/sports/2008/9/3/BasketballFacilities.aspx?id=1668 | title = Men's and Women's Basketball Facilities | publisher = [[Augustana University]] | accessdate = 2010-05-06}}</ref> The building is also the recreational center for the university and a host of several late night events. The Elmen Center is 81,000 square feet.<ref name=Augie1/>
The Elmen Center was completed in 1989.<ref name=Augie1/> Previously, Augustana basketball games were held at the [[Sioux Falls Arena]]. In 2000, the Elmen Center was the location of the NCAA Division II Elite 8 volleyball tournament.<ref name=Augie1/>
In addition to sports, the building can be used as a venue for concerts.<ref>Kirschenmann, Jay. ''Lifelight Tour bringing Christian music to Augustana amid 12 stops in 11 days'' [http://www.argusleader.com/article/20100408/ENT/4080327/Lifelight-Tour-bringing-Christian-music-to-Augustana-amid-12-stops-in-11-days] ''[[Argus Leader]]''. April 8, 2010. (accessed 2010-05-06)</ref>
On October 15, 2009, a fire broke out in the building after an object was left on hot equipment in the sauna.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ksfy.com/news/local/64465267.html | title = Fire at Elmen Center at Augustana College | publisher = [[KSFY]] | accessdate = 2010-05-06}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.keloland.com/NewsDetail6162.cfm?Id=0,91363 | title = Fire on Augustana College Campus | publisher = [[KELO-TV]] | accessdate = 2010-05-06}}</ref> The fire resulted in the building's evacuation and about $25,000 in damage.<ref>{{Cite web | last = Lockhart | first = Jenny |author2=Green, Rob. | title = Elmen Center fire shocks Augustana campus | publisher = ''The Augustana Mirror'' | date = 2009-10-22 | url = http://www.augustanamirror.com/news/elmen-center-fire-shocks-campus-1.2032058 | accessdate = 2010-05-06}}</ref>
In 2014 Augustana University agreed to a new deal which moved Men's and Women's doubleheaders into the Sioux Falls Arena, The Elmen Center now only hosts single basketball games, along with volleyball and wrestling matches.
