{{Infobox football biography | name = Ryan Casciaro | image = Ryan Casciaro (cropped).jpg | caption = Ryan Casciaro at the [[Victoria Stadium (Gibraltar)|Victoria Stadium]] in March 2014 | fullname = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|5|11|df=y}} | birth_place = Gibraltar | height = | currentclub = [[St Joseph's F.C.|St Joseph's]] | clubnumber = 2 | position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Rock Wolves | years1 = 2000–2006 | clubs1 = [[Gibraltar United F.C.|Gibraltar United]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2006–2018 | clubs2 = [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]] | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 2018– | clubs3 = [[St Joseph's F.C.|St Joseph's]] | caps3 = 7 | goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2013– | nationalteam1 = [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] | nationalcaps1= 24 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = 19:52, 27 November 2018 (UTC+2) | ntupdate = 25 March 2018 }}
'''Ryan Casciaro''' (born 11 May 1984) is a Gibraltarian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Gibraltar Premier Division]] side [[St Joseph's F.C.|St Joseph's]] and the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] national team, where he plays as a [[defender (association football)|defender]]. After spending the majoriy of his senior career at [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]], he joined [[St Joseph's F.C.|St Joseph's]] on 5 August 2018.
==International career== Casciaro made his international debut with Gibraltar on 19 November 2013 in a 0-0 home draw with [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://footballgibraltar.wordpress.com/2013/11/20/gibraltar-0-0-slovakia-extended-match-report/ | title=Gibraltar 0-0 Slovakia – extended match report | work=footballgibraltar.wordpress.com/ | accessdate=21 November 2013}}</ref> This was Gibraltar's first game since being admitted to [[UEFA]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/qualifiers/news/newsid=2024868.html | title=Gibraltar hold Slovakia in maiden international | publisher=www.uefa.com | accessdate=21 November 2013}}</ref>
===International career statistics=== {{updated|match played 25 March 2018.}} {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center" ! colspan=5 | [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar national team]] |- !Year!!Apps!!Goals |- |- |2013||1||0 |- |2014||8||0 |- |2015||5||0 |- |2016||7||0 |- |2017||2||0 |- |2018||1||0 |- !Total||24||0 |}
==Personal life== Casciaro is a policeman for the [[Gibraltar Defence Police]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Gibraltar v Poland: Starting XIs by professional occupation|url=http://i100.independent.co.uk/article/gibraltar-v-poland-starting-xis-by-professional-occupation--l13c2aPE4g|accessdate=9 September 2014|publisher=The Independent}}</ref> His brothers [[Kyle Casciaro|Kyle]] and [[Lee Casciaro|Lee]] have also played with Gibraltar's national side.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.marca.com/en/2015/03/30/en/football/international_football/1427666595.html |title=A policeman goes down in Gibraltar history |newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |date=30 Mar 2015 |accessdate=9 Oct 2016}}</ref>
