{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = The Parks | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Godmanchester]], [[Huntingdonshire]] | establishment = {{circa|1972}} | coord = {{coord|52.3217|-0.1709|display=inline}} | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 2000&ndash;2001 | club1 = [[Huntingdonshire County Cricket Club|Huntingdonshire]] | date = 2 July | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/496.html Ground profile }}
'''The Parks''' is a [[cricket]] ground situated off Fox Grove, [[Godmanchester]], [[Huntingdonshire]]. The ground is bordered to the north and south by residential housing and to the east by the [[A14 road (England)|A14 road]].
==History== Established between 1959 and 1972, the ground plays host to the home matches of Godmanchester Town Cricket Club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/496.html|title=Ground profile: The Parks, Godmanchester|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref> [[Huntingdonshire County Cricket Club|Huntingdonshire]] played two [[List A cricket|List A]] matches at the ground in the early 2000s, against the [[Yorkshire Cricket Board]] in the [[2000 NatWest Trophy]] and the [[Gloucestershire Cricket Board]] in the [[2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/496_a.html|title=List A Matches played on The Parks, Godmanchester|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref> with both matches ending in five wicket defeats for Huntingdonshire. The county also played a single [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] match at The Parks in 2001 against the [[Essex Cricket Board]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/496_mint.html|title=Minor Counties Trophy Matches played on The Parks, Godmanchester|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref> Huntingdonshire soon after lost List A status and were excluded from the MCCA Knockout Trophy,{{#tag:ref|Although considered one of the twenty-two [[Minor counties of English and Welsh cricket]], Huntingdonshire never entered a team into any minor counties competitions until 1998, when it entered a team into the MCCA Knockout Trophy, while the following year it entered a team into the [[Friends Provident Trophy|domestic List A competition]]. It continued to play in both competitions until 2002, after which the decision was taken to reduce the size of both competitions, with Huntingdonshire alongside the Cricket Boards of the [[first-class cricket|first-class counties]] being excluded from future competitions|group=n}} but have continued to play in minor fixtures at the ground.
==Records== ===List A=== * '''Highest team total:''' 207/5 (45 overs) by [[Yorkshire Cricket Board]] v [[Huntingdonshire County Cricket Club|Huntingdonshire]], 2000<ref name="SCORE1">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/69/69747.html|title=Huntingdonshire v Yorkshire Cricket Board, 2000 NatWest Trophy|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref> * '''Lowest team total:''' 180/8 (50 overs) by Huntingdonshire v [[Gloucestershire Cricket Board]], 2001<ref name="SCORE2">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/72/72862.html|title=Huntingdonshire v Gloucestershire Cricket Board, 2002 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref> * '''Highest individual innings:''' 75 by [[Neil Stovold]], as above<ref name="SCORE2"/> * '''Best bowling in an innings:''' 3/36 by [[James Rendell]], as above<ref name="SCORE2"/>
